---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Project.astro";
import Heading from "@/components/ui/Heading.astro";
import Text from "@/components/ui/Text.astro";
import ProjectContnetWrapper from "@/components/ui/ProjectContnetWrapper.astro";
import SwiperSlider from "@/components/ui/SwiperSlider.astro";
import { loadImages } from "@/utils/loadImages";

import detail1Img from "@/assets/alfaDecor/4.png";
import detail2Img from "@/assets/alfaDecor/5.png";
import logoImg from "@/assets/logo/alfalogo-min.png";

const title = "Alfa Bank - Alfa Travel";
const years = "2023-2025";

const imageModulesFirst = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "/src/assets/alfa1/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif}"
);
const imageModulesSecond = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "/src/assets/alfa2/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif}"
);
const imageModulesThird = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "/src/assets/alfa3/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif}"
);

const sliderImagesFirst = await loadImages(imageModulesFirst);
const sliderImagesSecond = await loadImages(imageModulesSecond);
const sliderImagesThird = await loadImages(imageModulesThird);
---

<Layout {title} {years} logo={logoImg}>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Text>
      Alfa-Bank is Russia's largest private bank, providing financial services
      to over 22 million customers through 672+ branches nationwide. As a
      universal bank, it offers comprehensive banking operations including
      retail, corporate banking, investment services, and digital solutions with
      approximately 25,000 employees.</Text
    >
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >Alfa Travel is the bank's integrated travel booking platform, providing
      comprehensive travel services including flights, hotels, train tickets,
      and vacation packages. The platform leverages the bank's ecosystem
      approach, allowing customers to utilize bonus points and rewards across
      all banking services while seamlessly booking and paying for travel
      through their existing banking relationship.</Text
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">How It Started</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      I joined the travel department as its first designer. Before that, the
      design was done by a designer from the partner company, since flight
      sales worked through the partner's API. Part of the flow was a white
      label, part was drawn by the partner's designer. When the product started
      to grow, it had to be brought up to the quality level of a large bank.
    </Text>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Why Me</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      I have a lot of experience in travel: I worked at OneTwoTrip, designed a
      train ticket app for former colleagues, made a website for a new airline
      and an in-flight entertainment service. I also run my own travel side
      project with 50k MAU.
    </Text>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">My Role</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      Sole designer in the travel department, working within Alfa Bank's
      design system across flight bookings, hotel reservations, train tickets,
      and vacation packages.
    </Text>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">First Steps</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      I started with research on the current state of the travel industry in
      Russia and worldwide. Then I began moving the site to new components,
      since the old ones were outdated, and in parallel made small interface
      fixes wherever I saw problems.
    </Text>
    <Heading
      class="mt-[100px] mb-[10px] text-[28px]"
      level={2}
      weight="semibold">A Few Key Projects & Solutions</Heading
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold"
      >Homepage Redesign & User Engagement</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >The homepage redesign started with people, not screens. I had calls with
      the heads of the travel business to collect their wishes and
      expectations. I also talked to the designer of the bank's main homepage
      and stayed in touch with them at every stage. For references I collected
      screenshots of homepages from major services in Russia and worldwide,
      partly through Mobbin.</Text
    >
    <Text class="mb-[25px]"
      >The main idea was to make the homepage more alive with travel
      recommendations: "Popular Destinations," "Popular Hotels," and "Popular
      Tours." Later we added an integration with Alfa Afisha, a service with
      events across Russia. The business team also asked for several promo
      banners. Since the design was a bento box, I prepared different grid
      layouts for different numbers of banners. I showed intermediate versions
      to stakeholders all the time, and we ran design reviews with the design
      team.</Text
    >
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <div class="mt-[40px] mb-[100px]">
    <SwiperSlider
      sliderImages={sliderImagesFirst}
      initialWidth="267px"
      video={true}
    />
  </div>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold"
      >Hotels & Personal Account</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      I designed the hotels booking flow from scratch and kept improving the
      personal account, where users manage their trips and tickets.
    </Text>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold"
      >Automated Ticket Services</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      Developed self-service ticket refund and exchange system with automated
      price difference calculations, eliminating the need for customer support
      intervention. This solution reduced support inquiries for ticket-related
      issues by <b>74.1%</b>, significantly improving operational efficiency
      while providing users with instant ticket management capabilities.
    </Text>
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <div class="mt-[40px] mb-[100px]">
    <SwiperSlider sliderImages={sliderImagesSecond} initialWidth="270px" />
  </div>
  <div class="mt-[40px] mb-[100px]">
    <SwiperSlider sliderImages={sliderImagesThird} initialWidth="270px" />
  </div>
  <div
    class="mt-[40px] mb-[100px] flex items-start gap-[40px] overflow-x-auto overflow-visible scroll-smooth snap-x snap-mandatory lg:snap-none no-scrollbar
      px-[var(--container-padding)] scroll-px-[var(--container-padding)] lg:px-[var(--offset-left)] lg:scroll-px-0 lg:pb-0"
    style=`--offset-left: calc(50vw - (1200px/2) + 270px + 20px)`
    tabindex="0"
    role="region"
    aria-label="Media carousel"
  >
    <Image
      src={detail1Img}
      width={detail1Img.width / 2}
      class="max-w-[none]"
      alt="Decorative detail image"
    />
  </div>
  <div
    class="mt-[40px] mb-[100px] flex items-start gap-[40px] overflow-x-auto overflow-visible scroll-smooth snap-x snap-mandatory lg:snap-none no-scrollbar
      px-[var(--container-padding)] scroll-px-[var(--container-padding)] lg:px-[var(--offset-left)] lg:scroll-px-0 lg:pb-0"
    style=`--offset-left: calc(50vw - (1200px/2) + 270px + 20px)`
    tabindex="0"
    role="region"
    aria-label="Media carousel"
  >
    <Image
      src={detail2Img}
      width={detail2Img.width / 2}
      class="max-w-[none]"
      alt="Decorative detail image"
    />
  </div>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold"
      >A/B Tests and Mentoring</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[50px]">
      I ran A/B tests on the important steps of the booking funnel to improve
      business metrics. When a middle designer joined the team, I onboarded
      them: distributed tasks and helped them understand the project and the
      design system.
    </Text>
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
</Layout>
